---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How SiliconFeed collects, uses, and protects information when you use siliconfeed.online."
  ogType="website"
  canonicalUrl="https://siliconfeed.online/privacy"
>
  <article class="glass static-page static-page--boxed">
    <h1 class="static-page__title">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="static-page__p static-page__legal-note">
      Effective date: April 8, 2026. This policy describes SiliconFeed’s practices for the website
      <strong>siliconfeed.online</strong>. It is provided for transparency and for integrations such as Google
      Publisher Center / advertising or subscription products. It is <strong>not</strong> legal advice; have counsel
      review it if you rely on it for compliance.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Who we are</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      SiliconFeed is an online publication (“we”, “us”). Contact:
      <a href="mailto:hello@siliconfeed.online">hello@siliconfeed.online</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">What we collect</h2>
    <ul class="static-page__list">
      <li>
        <strong>Usage and technical data.</strong> When you visit the site, our hosting and infrastructure providers may
        process IP address, browser type, device type, approximate location, referrer, and similar technical data in
        server logs for security, reliability, and abuse prevention.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Analytics.</strong> We may use Google Analytics (or similar services) to understand aggregate traffic
        (e.g. pages viewed, session duration). These tools may set cookies or use similar technologies as described in
        their own policies.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Content you send us.</strong> If you email us or contact us through a third-party service, we receive
        whatever information you choose to provide (e.g. email address, message content).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Newsletter / email list.</strong> If we offer a mailing list, we process the address you submit and
        related subscription metadata to send messages; you can unsubscribe using the link in those emails where
        applicable.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      We and our partners may use cookies, local storage, or pixels where needed for the site to function, for
      analytics, or—if enabled—for advertising, measurement, or subscription features. You can control cookies through
      your browser settings; blocking some cookies may limit site functionality.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">How we use information</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">We use the information above to operate and improve the site, measure audience and performance, secure our
      services, comply with law, and—if applicable—deliver ads or subscriber experiences through authorized partners.</p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Third parties</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      We rely on vendors for hosting (e.g. Vercel), analytics (e.g. Google), databases or APIs where the product
      requires them, and possibly ad or subscription platforms (e.g. Google). Those providers process data under their
      own terms and privacy policies. We do not sell your personal information in the conventional sense of selling
      lists of individuals; where “sale” or “sharing” is defined broadly by law (e.g. for cross-context behavioral
      advertising), we will align disclosures and choices with applicable requirements.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Retention</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      We keep information only as long as needed for the purposes above, unless a longer period is required by law.
      Log and analytics retention depend on provider defaults and our configuration.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Your rights</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or restrict certain processing, or
      to object to processing. To exercise rights or ask questions, contact us at
      <a href="mailto:hello@siliconfeed.online">hello@siliconfeed.online</a>. We may need to verify your request.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Children</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      The site is not directed at children under 16. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children as
      defined by applicable law.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">International visitors</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      If you access the site from outside the United States, your information may be processed in the United States or
      other countries where our providers operate.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Changes</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      We may update this policy from time to time. The “Effective date” at the top will change when we do; continued use
      of the site after updates means you accept the revised policy where the law allows.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
